### Packages and libraries to use

* When an utility function has potential of reuse, put it in appropriate existing .go file or subfolder in /common. Only create new file or subfolder in /common when neccesary.

* You must look into /common folder and its subfolders to find reusable utility functions. For example use ToPtr() in /common/util/type.go to convert a scalar to pointer.

* Always use functions from "go.bryk.io/pkg/errors" to create new or wrap errors instead of using fmt.Errors() or standard "errors" package. Only use standard "errors" package for the Join() function. The correct way to use standard "errors" is:

    ```go
    import (
        "errors" stdErr
    )
    ```

